  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nSo, it looks like our use of `apollo-server` v2 in Truffle DB is responsible for multiple of the warnings that people are seeing when they install Truffle.  I think if we upgraded to v3, we could cut down on those warnings a little.  Of course, v3 has breaking changes from v2, but it sounds like they shouldn't be too bad?  FWIW, here's [the migration guide](https://www.apollographql.com/docs/apollo-server/migration/) and the [list of breaking changes from the 3.0.0 release notes](https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-server/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md#breaking-changes).\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.4.29",
